Actress Beverly Naya has said the resilient nature of Nigerians is a thing to be proud about yet calls for great concerns. The British-born filmmaker explained Nigerians despite having had it tough the previous day are able to pick up themselves the next day like nothing ever happened. Using an oxymoron to emphasise her point, Naya described the attribute as both a ‘blessing and curse’.   Next album will be different, special – Mr Eazi     Instagram bans Kanye West for 24 hours     2022 AMVCA holds May 14   “Yesterday was a very tough day for Nigerians, but today feels like any regular day”, she tweeted. “I don’t know how we’re this resilient as a people, but it’s a blessing and most definitely a curse,” she wrote on Twitter.